roughout the chapters. But the chapters themselves remind us of the importance of local conditions, despite the global pressures of the 21st century, in imagining and creating multilingual educational spaces.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEducation, BilingualvCross-cultural studies. 0aGlobalizationvCross-cultural studies. 0aLanguage and educationvCross-cultural studies. 0aMulticultural educationvCross-cultural studies. 0aMultilingualismvCross-cultural studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aCummins, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Viv, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEscamilla, Kathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEtxeberría-Sagastume, Feli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHornberger, Nancy H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHélot, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez, Luis Enrique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarty, Teresa L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohanty, Ajit K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewcombe, Lynda Pritchard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNyati-Ramahobo, Lydia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOgulnick, Karen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRomero, Mary Eunice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ct